  'q_az_az-specific-road-rules-and-quirks_0', 'quiz_az_az-specific-road-rules-and-quirks', 'Under Arizona''s "Stupid Motorist Law," what can happen if you drive around a barricade into a flooded roadway and need to be rescued?', '["Nothing — emergency rescues are always free","You receive a warning on your first offense only","You can be charged the full cost of the rescue, plus a traffic citation","Your vehicle is automatically impounded for 30 days"]', 2, 'Arizona''s Stupid Motorist Law allows authorities to bill the driver for the full cost of emergency rescue when they bypass barricades to enter a flooded area.', 0
