  'q_fl_florida-specific-road-rules-and-quirks_0', 'quiz_fl_florida-specific-road-rules-and-quirks', 'Under Florida''s Move Over Law on a multi-lane highway, what must you do when approaching a stopped emergency vehicle with flashing lights?', '["Maintain speed and stay in your lane","Stop completely until the emergency vehicle leaves","Change lanes away from the stopped vehicle if safe; otherwise slow to 20 mph below the limit","Honk to alert the emergency personnel"]', 2, 'On a multi-lane road you must move over if it is safe. If you cannot, you must reduce speed to 20 mph below the posted limit (5 mph if the limit is 20 or less).', 0
