at 14 -> Intermediate License at 16 (after holding the permit for at least 12 months with no convictions in the prior 6 months) -> Full License at 17. Driver education is required for anyone under 18 seeking a license and must include 30 hours classroom plus 6 hours behind-the-wheel. Parents must certify 20 hours of supervised practice (at least 2 hours at night) before the intermediate license is issued.","needsReview":["Exact age threshold for Minor School License (commonly 14.5 but verify current statute)","Whether the 20-hour parent-certified practice requirement still mandates a specific nighttime minimum","Confirm 2025 hands-free law effective date and exact statutory citation","Verify the conviction-free window (6 months) required before intermediate license issuance","Confirm passenger restriction wording - some sources describe the ''one unrelated minor'' rule differently"]}}', unixepoch('now')*1000, 'Generated; school must review and tweak.', unixepoch('now')*1000
