INSERT OR REPLACE INTO lesson (id, moduleId, slug, title, body, estimatedSeatMinutes, ordinal) VALUES (
  'lesson_ia_how-to-get-an-iowa-instruction-permit', 'module_ia_overlay', 'how-to-get-an-iowa-instruction-permit', 'How to Get an Iowa Instruction Permit', '# Getting Your Iowa Instruction Permit

Iowa is one of the few states in the country where you can begin driving legally at age 14. The first credential on your journey is the **Instruction Permit**, issued by the Iowa Department of Transportation (Iowa DOT) Motor Vehicle Division. This lesson walks you through eligibility, required documents, the testing process, and what the permit allows you to do.

## Who is eligible

To apply for an Iowa Instruction Permit you must be:

- At least **14 years old** on the day you apply.
- Enrolled in (or have completed) an approved Iowa driver education course, OR be enrolled in an approved course at the time of application. Anyone under 18 seeking a license must complete driver education that includes **30 hours of classroom instruction** and **6 hours of behind-the-wheel** training with an Iowa-approved instructor.
- Able to provide proof of identity, Iowa residency, Social Security number, and parent/guardian consent if under 18.

## Documents to bring to the DOT service center

Iowa requires you to verify your identity in person. Bring:

1. **Proof of identity and date of birth** - certified birth certificate or U.S. passport.
2. **Proof of Social Security number** - Social Security card, W-2, or pay stub showing your full SSN.
3. **Two proofs of Iowa residency** - utility bill, bank statement, school record, or similar documents showing your Iowa address.
4. **Parent or legal guardian** must be present (or provide a notarized consent form) to sign for any applicant under 18.
5. **Driver education enrollment or completion certificate** if you''ve started or finished the course.
6. The **application fee** - currently a few dollars for the permit itself.

## The tests

At the service center you will take:

- A **vision screening** (you can wear glasses or contacts).
- A **knowledge test** covering Iowa traffic laws, road signs, and safe driving practices. The Iowa Driver''s Manual is the official study source.
- A **sign recognition test** built into the knowledge exam.

You do **not** take a behind-the-wheel road test for the instruction permit - that test comes later, when you upgrade to an intermediate license.

## What the permit lets you do

An Iowa Instruction Permit allows you to drive **only** when a licensed driver who is at least 21 years old (or a parent/guardian/spouse who is at least 18) is seated next to you in the front seat. You must hold the permit for **at least 12 months** with no traffic convictions in the most recent 6 months before you are eligible to apply for an intermediate license at age 16.

During the permit phase you and a parent or guardian must log at least **20 hours of supervised driving practice**, including a portion at night. Iowa requires the parent to certify these hours on an official form when you apply for the intermediate license.

## The Minor School License option

If you live more than one mile from your school and are at least about 14.5 years old, you may qualify for an Iowa **Minor School License** (often called a school permit). This is a restricted license that lets you drive yourself to and from school activities along designated routes. School officials and a parent must approve the application. The school license is unique to states like Iowa that have large rural populations.

## Next steps

Once you have the permit, focus on building real-world driving experience with your supervising adult. Track every hour. Stay free of tickets. After 12 months, you can move to the intermediate license stage covered in the next lesson.', 45, 0
);
