INSERT OR REPLACE INTO lesson (id, moduleId, slug, title, body, estimatedSeatMinutes, ordinal) VALUES (
  'lesson_la_how-to-get-a-louisiana-permit', 'module_la_overlay', 'how-to-get-a-louisiana-permit', 'How to Get Your Louisiana Temporary Instructional Permit', '## Welcome to Louisiana''s Graduated Driver License Program

Louisiana''s path to a full driver''s license is a three-stage Graduated Driver License (GDL) program administered by the **Office of Motor Vehicles (OMV)**, a division of the Department of Public Safety. Stage one is the **Temporary Instructional Permit (TIP)**, sometimes just called the learner''s permit. This lesson walks you through everything you need to obtain it.

### Step 1: Meet the Age Requirement

You must be at least **15 years old** to apply for a TIP in Louisiana. There is no upper age limit, but the document requirements differ if you are under 18 (a minor) versus 18 or older.

### Step 2: Complete Driver Education

Applicants under 18 must complete a **state-approved 30-hour classroom course plus 8 hours of behind-the-wheel (BTW) instruction** with a licensed Louisiana driving school. This is commonly called the **38-hour course**. The classroom hours can be delivered in-person or through an OMV-approved online program, but the 8 BTW hours must be conducted in a vehicle with a licensed instructor.

Applicants who are 18 or older have a shorter option: a **6-hour pre-licensing course**. Many adults still choose the full 38-hour course because it provides much more practice.

### Step 3: Gather Your Documents

When you visit the OMV, bring:

- **Proof of identity**: certified birth certificate or valid U.S. passport
- **Social Security card** (or a document showing your SSN)
- **Two proofs of Louisiana residency** dated within the last six months (utility bill, bank statement, school records). If you are a minor, your parent''s documents typically work.
- **Proof of school enrollment** or a high school equivalency (HiSET/GED). Louisiana ties driving privileges to school attendance for minors.
- **Driver education completion certificate** issued by your licensed school
- **Parent or legal guardian signature** on the minor''s application — the parent must appear in person or provide a notarized form
- **Payment** for the application fee (currently around $32, subject to change)

### Step 4: Pass the Knowledge and Vision Tests

At the OMV field office (or an authorized third-party tester), you will take:

- A **vision screening** (20/40 in at least one eye, with or without corrective lenses)
- A **40-question written knowledge test** based on the Louisiana Class E Driver''s Guide. You must score **80% or higher** (32 of 40 correct). The test covers road signs, right-of-way, GDL restrictions, and impaired-driving laws.

Many Louisiana driving schools administer the knowledge test in-house as part of the 38-hour course, which can save you a trip.

### Step 5: Hold the Permit for at Least Six Months

Once issued, the TIP must be held for a **minimum of 180 days (6 months)** before you can move to the next stage. During this period you must:

- Always drive with a **licensed adult 21 or older** seated in the front passenger seat
- Log supervised driving practice (Louisiana strongly recommends 50 hours, including some night driving)
- Avoid any moving violations — a conviction will restart your six-month clock

### Step 6: Move to the Intermediate License

At **16**, after holding the TIP for six months with a clean record and completing your BTW hours, you can apply for the **Intermediate License**. This stage carries the nighttime and passenger restrictions covered in the next lesson, and ends at age 17 when you become eligible for a full Class E license.

### Common Mistakes to Avoid

- Letting your parent sign the application without bringing valid ID for themselves
- Forgetting that school enrollment proof is required for minors
- Assuming an online-only course is enough — the 8 BTW hours are mandatory under 18
- Driving outside the supervised conditions during the TIP phase, which can void the permit', 35, 0
);
