  'q_la_louisiana-specific-rules-and-quirks_1', 'quiz_la_louisiana-specific-rules-and-quirks', 'Under Louisiana''s Move-Over law, if you cannot safely change lanes away from a stopped emergency vehicle, what must you do?', '["Continue at the posted speed limit","Stop completely until the vehicle leaves","Slow to at least 25 mph below the posted speed limit (or 10 mph if the limit is under 25)","Honk to alert the emergency crew"]', 2, 'If you can''t safely change lanes, you must reduce speed to at least 25 mph below the posted limit (10 mph below if the limit is under 25 mph).', 1
