  'rpv_md_teen_1_0_0', 'rp_md_teen', '1.0.0', '{"credentials":[{"key":"permit_eligibility","label":"Learner''s Permit","deliveryMode":"manual"}],"requirements":[{"key":"classroom_hours","label":"Classroom hours","target":30,"unit":"hour"},{"key":"btw_hours","label":"Behind-the-wheel hours","target":6,"unit":"hour"},{"key":"supervised_practice_hours","label":"Supervised practice (parent log)","target":60,"unit":"hour"}],"rules":[{"key":"unlock_permit_eligibility","trigger":"enrollment.state_changed","conditions":{"jurisdiction":"US-MD","minPermitAge":15.75,"classroomHoursCompleted":{"gte":30}},"actions":[{"type":"unlock_credential","credential":"permit_eligibility"},{"type":"set_journey_state","value":"permit_eligible"}]}],"facts":{"agencyName":"Maryland Motor Vehicle Administration (MVA)","minPermitAge":15.75,"minLicenseAge":16.5,"minPermitDurationMonths":9,"nighttimeRestriction":"Provisional license holders may not drive between midnight and 5:00 a.m. unless accompanied by a qualified supervising driver age 21+ with at least 3 years of licensed driving experience, or for specific exemptions (employment, school, organized athletic events, volunteer fire/EMS).","passengerRestriction":"During the first 5 months of a provisional license, the driver may not transport passengers under age 18 unless accompanied by a qualified supervising driver age 21+, or unless the passengers are immediate family members.","cellPhoneRule":"Drivers under 18 with a learner''s permit or provisional license are prohibited from using any handheld or hands-free wireless communication device while driving, except to call 911. All Maryland drivers are banned from texting and from holding a handheld phone while driving.","notes":"Maryland operates a Rookie Driver Graduated Licensing program with three stages: learner''s permit, provisional license, and full license. Driver education (30 hours classroom + 6 hours behind-the-wheel) must be completed at an MVA-certified driver education provider before the skills (road) test. The 60 supervised practice hours must be documented on a Practice and Skills Log signed by a parent/guardian (10 of those hours must be at night). The learner''s permit must be held for a minimum of 9 months with no convictions before applying for a provisional license. Maryland does not use a separate ''permit card'' name—it is simply called a Learner''s Permit, which is a temporary credential issued by the MVA.","needsReview":["Exact minPermitAge — Maryland statute states 15 years 9 months; encoded as 15.75 but confirm decimal handling for fractional ages.","Whether the 10 required nighttime supervised hours should be tracked as a separate field rather than embedded in notes.","Provisional license conviction-free period (currently 9 months but should be re-verified against current MD transportation code).","Whether ''manual'' is the correct delivery mode — MVA accepts driver-ed completion certificates electronically from certified schools (DE-supplied via MVA''s Driver Education portal); could be ''electronic_upload'' or ''api'' depending on integration."]}}', unixepoch('now')*1000, 'Generated; school must review and tweak.', unixepoch('now')*1000
);
