  'rpv_ny_teen_1_0_0', 'rp_ny_teen', '1.0.0', '{"credentials":[{"key":"permit_eligibility","label":"Learner Permit","deliveryMode":"manual"}],"requirements":[{"key":"classroom_hours","label":"Classroom hours","target":24,"unit":"hour"},{"key":"btw_hours","label":"Behind-the-wheel hours","target":0,"unit":"hour"},{"key":"supervised_practice_hours","label":"Supervised practice (parent log)","target":50,"unit":"hour"}],"rules":[{"key":"unlock_permit_eligibility","trigger":"enrollment.state_changed","conditions":{"jurisdiction":"US-NY","minPermitAge":16,"classroomHoursCompleted":{"gte":24}},"actions":[{"type":"unlock_credential","credential":"permit_eligibility"},{"type":"set_journey_state","value":"permit_eligible"}]}],"facts":{"agencyName":"New York State Department of Motor Vehicles (NYSDMV)","minPermitAge":16,"minLicenseAge":16.5,"minPermitDurationMonths":6,"nighttimeRestriction":"Junior permit/license holders generally cannot drive between 9:00 PM and 5:00 AM unless with a parent/guardian, supervising driver, or for limited approved purposes. In New York City, junior permits/licenses are not valid at all.","passengerRestriction":"Junior license holders under 18 may carry no more than one passenger under age 21 unless the additional passengers are immediate family members.","cellPhoneRule":"All drivers are prohibited from using a handheld mobile phone or texting while driving. Junior permit/license holders face heightened penalties including mandatory suspension for a first cell phone or texting conviction.","notes":"New York operates a Graduated Driver License (GDL) system with distinct Junior (Class DJ/MJ) and Senior (Class D/M) credentials. The minimum age for a learner permit is 16. Driver education is not mandatory but completing a NY State-approved high school or commercial driver education course (typically 24+ classroom and 24 in-car/observation hours, often offered through Driving School License (DSL) programs) earns a Certificate of Completion (MV-285) that allows applicants to take the road test at 16.5 (versus 17 without it) and lifts certain junior restrictions once a senior license is issued. A 5-hour Pre-Licensing Course (MV-278) or equivalent driver ed is required before the road test. New York City has unique rules: junior permits and junior licenses (DJ/MJ) are NOT valid for driving in any of the five boroughs of NYC (Manhattan, Bronx, Brooklyn, Queens, Staten Island), and on Long Island, junior license holders face additional restrictions. A 50-hour supervised practice log (form MV-262), including at least 15 hours after sunset, is required before the road test.","needsReview":["Whether the minLicenseAge of 16.5 with driver ed certificate is correctly captured (without driver ed it is 17; junior license without restrictions/upgrade to senior license is at 18)","Exact classroom hours requirement — 24 reflects typical commercial driver ed; the mandatory state Pre-Licensing Course is only 5 hours","Whether requiredBtwHours of 0 is correct — NY does not mandate BTW hours for licensure but driver ed programs typically include in-car instruction","Whether NYC restriction applies to all junior permit holders practicing or only to unsupervised driving","Specific penalty durations for cell phone violations by junior drivers"]}}', unixepoch('now')*1000, 'Generated; school must review and tweak.', unixepoch('now')*1000
);
