  'q_sc_sc-specific-rules-and-quirks_0', 'quiz_sc_sc-specific-rules-and-quirks', 'Under SC''s Move Over Law, what must you do when approaching a stationary tow truck with flashing lights?', '["Continue at posted speed; the law only covers police and EMS","Move one lane away if safe, or slow below the posted limit","Stop completely until the vehicle leaves","Honk to alert the workers, then proceed normally"]', 1, 'SC''s Move Over Law applies to any stationary vehicle with flashing lights — including tow trucks — and requires moving over a lane or slowing below the speed limit.', 0
